# Testing (Vitest)

## What to test

- **Primary target:** pure functions in `src/features/`.
- Place tests in `tests/unit/` mirroring feature names (e.g. `invite-links.test.ts`).

## Running tests

```bash
pnpm test          # CI / pre-PR
pnpm test:watch    # local iteration
```

## Invite URL cases

Cover when touching invite logic:

- `https://halisaha.cc/invite/match/CODE` and `/invite/group/CODE`
- `halisaha://invite/match/CODE` scheme URLs
- Invalid / partial paths return `null`
- `encodeURIComponent` round-trip for special characters

## Auth callback cases

Cover when touching `parse-callback.ts`:

- Hash vs query param parsing
- `type=recovery`, `signup`, `email_change`
- Error descriptions and deep link builder output

## Style

- Use descriptive `it()` / `describe()` names.
- No snapshot tests for simple string/url logic — assert exact values.
